Kano &mdash; A Senior Magistrates Court in Kano has granted bail to Kano based Hausa musician, Sadiq Usman Saleh, popularly known as Sadiq Zazzabi.The musician was arraigned before Magistrate Aliyu Gabari last week by the Kano State Censorship Board over an uncensored song and indecent dress.Saleh spent the weekend in custody as the court failed to sit on Friday.Magistrate Gabari granted the musician bail in the sum of N100,000 and two sureties one of which must be a member of the music writers association of Kano State, and the other a civil servant of not lower than grade level 14.The court adjourned till March 27, 2017 for continuation will continuation.